README - quick run

Project structure:
- backend/
    - app.py
    - requirements.txt
    - model/ (place .pkl files here)
- frontend/
    - index.html
    - main.js
    - styles.css

Steps to run locally (Linux / macOS). On Windows adapt venv activation.

1) Backend
$ cd backend
$ python3 -m venv venv
$ source venv/bin/activate
(venv) $ pip install -r requirements.txt
(venv) $ uvicorn app:app --reload --port 8000

Check health:
$ curl http://127.0.0.1:8000/health

2) Frontend (static)
Open another terminal and serve frontend folder:
$ cd frontend
# Option A: quick python server
$ python3 -m http.server 5173
# Open http://127.0.0.1:5173 in browser and test.

# Option B: use Live Server extension in VS Code to serve frontend.

Swapping models:
- To use SVM fallback: put `lyrics_genre_linearSVC_calibrated.pkl` into backend/model/
- To use final SBERT+SVM: put `final_sbert_svm_ensemble_w0.5.pkl` (bundle saved with keys: "svm_with_proba", "clf_sbert", "sbert_model_name", "ensemble_weight", "classes") into backend/model/
- After replacing file, restart uvicorn server.

Deployment:
- Backend: Render / Railway / Heroku (use uvicorn command)
- Frontend: Vercel / Netlify (deploy static site)

